/Users/prashanthvarma/Saturn/internal/as.name: CreateQuestionRequest
/Users/prashanthvarma/Saturn/internal/as.description:
Request to create a question resource.

Attributes:
    parent (str):
        Required. The name of the project this data source reference
        belongs to. Example: ``projects/foo/locations/bar``
    question (google.cloud.dataqna_v1alpha.types.Question):
        Required. The question to create.

parent.description: Required. The name of the project this data source reference belongs to. Example: ``projects/foo/locations/bar``

name.description: Output only. Immutable. The unique identifier for the Question. The ID is server-generated. Example: ``projects/foo/locations/bar/questions/123``

scopes.description: Required. Immutable. Scopes to be used for the question. A scope defines the relevant data set scope. It can be a reference to a specific data source or a collection of data sources. Currently, support is limited to a single BigQuery table. There must be exactly one ``scopes`` element.  Example: ``//bigquery.googleapis.com/projects/test-project/datasets/foo/tables/bar``

query.description: Required. Immutable. The query in natural language.

data_source_annotations.description: A list of annotations to use instead of the default annotation of a data source (set in the data source reference resource). There must not be more than one annotation with the same data source reference.

interpret_error.description: An error field explaining why interpretation failed. This is only populated if the interpretation failed.  Note: This is different from getting a status error on the request itself. This is not a client or server error and the Question resource is still persisted, but the service could not interpret the question. Clients should present the error to the user so the user can rephrase the question.

message.description: Error message explaining why this question could not be interpreted.

code.description: The code for the error category why the interpretation failed.

unsupported_details.description: Populated if parts of the query are unsupported.

incomplete_query_details.description: Populated if the query is incomplete.

ambiguity_details.description: Populated if the query was too ambiguous.

interpretations.description: A list of interpretations for this question.

data_sources.description: List of data sources used in the current understanding.

confidence.description: The level of confidence that one of the interpretations is correct. This is a value in the range [0, 1] where a value of 0.5 or below is to be considered a low confidence.

unused_phrases.description: A list of unused phrases. Clients should display a Did You Mean (DYM)  dialog if this is non-empty, even if this is the only interpretation.

human_readable.description: Human readable representation of the query.

html_formatted.description: HTML version of the string annotation.

markups.description: Semantic version of the string annotation.

type_.description: The semantic type of the markup substring.

start_char_index.description: Unicode character index of the query.

length.description: The length (number of unicode characters) of the markup substring.

html_formatted.description: HTML version of the string annotation.

markups.description: Semantic version of the string annotation.

type_.description: The semantic type of the markup substring.

start_char_index.description: Unicode character index of the query.

length.description: The length (number of unicode characters) of the markup substring.

interpretation_structure.description: Information about the interpretation structure that helps to understand and visualize the response.

visualization_types.description: List of possible visualization types to apply for this interpretation. The order has no relevance.

column_info.description: Information about the output columns, that is, the columns that will be returned by the backend.

output_alias.description: The alias of the output column as used by the backend. For example, the field name in the schema provided in the query response in BigQuery.

display_name.description: Human readable name of the output column.

data_query.description: Representation of the data query to be sent to the backend.

sql.description: The generated SQL query to be sent to the backend.

execution_info.description: Information about the backend response. This is populated only if execution of an interpretation was requested.

job_creation_status.description: Status returned by the backend when the job was created.

state.description: Output only. State of the metadata job.

message.description: Output only. Message relating to the progression of a metadata job.

update_time.description: Output only. The time when the status was updated.

create_time.description: Time when the execution was triggered.

bigquery_job.description: BigQuery job information. Future versions will have different backends. Hence, clients must make sure they can handle it when this field is not populated.

project_id.description: The project ID of the job.

location.description: The location where the job is running.

create_time.description: Time when the question was created.

user_email.description: Output only. The e-mail address of the user that created this question.

debug_flags.description: Input only. Immutable. Flags to request additional information for debugging purposes.

include_va_query.description: Whether to include the original VAQuery.

include_nested_va_query.description: Whether to include the original nested VAQuery.

include_human_interpretation.description: Whether to include the original human interpretation strings generated by Analyza.

include_aqua_debug_response.description: Whether to include the Aqua debug response.

time_override.description: The time in milliseconds from Unix epoch to be used to process the query. This is useful for testing the queries at different time period. If not set or time_override <= 0, then the current time is used.

is_internal_google_user.description: Set to true if request is initiated by an internal Google user.

ignore_cache.description: Determines whether cache needs to be ignored. If set to true, cache won't be queried and updated.

include_search_entities_rpc.description: Whether to include the request/response pair from the call to the EntityIndex for SearchEntities.

include_list_column_annotations_rpc.description: Whether to include the request/response pair from the call to the Annotations service for ListColumnAnnotations.

include_virtual_analyst_entities.description: Whether to include the entity list passed to Analyza.

include_table_list.description: Whether to include the table list.

include_domain_list.description: Whether to include the domain list.

debug_info.description: Top level debug information. This will be stored as the type DebugInformation. Using Any so clients don't need to pull in anything inside the debug message.

Request for query suggestions.

Attributes:

        Required. The parent of the suggestion query
        is the resource denoting the project and
        location.

        The scopes to which this search is restricted. The only
        supported scope pattern is
        ``//bigquery.googleapis.com/projects/{GCP-PROJECT-ID}/datasets/{DATASET-ID}/tables/{TABLE-ID}``.

        User query for which to generate suggestions.

        suggestions right away, helping the user to get

        The requested suggestion type. Multiple
        suggestion types can be requested, but there is
        no guarantee that the service will return

parent.description: Required. The parent of the suggestion query is the resource denoting the project and location.

scopes.description: The scopes to which this search is restricted. The only supported scope pattern is ``//bigquery.googleapis.com/projects/{GCP-PROJECT-ID}/datasets/{DATASET-ID}/tables/{TABLE-ID}``.

query.description: User query for which to generate suggestions. If the query is empty, zero state suggestions are returned. This allows UIs to display suggestions right away, helping the user to get a sense of what a query might look like.

suggestion_types.description: The requested suggestion type. Multiple suggestion types can be requested, but there is no guarantee that the service will return suggestions for each type.
